summary: How I think the Tyrus getting together scene will go
body:
How I think the Tyrus getting together scene will go

*on the bench five feet appart cuz they’re not gay*

Tj: is there anything you want to tell me?

Cyrus: Tj I- listen i know you might not feel the same way but also you’re my friend and I want you to know but I also don’t want to scare you off, please promise that whatever I’m about to say that we’ll still be friends?

Tj: *gets closer to Cyrus grabs his hand and squeezes it* Cyrus, you’re my best friend and I know I’ve said it before but you’re the only person I can talk to like this. No matter what you say I’m right next to you.

Cyrus: *whispering* Tj, I like you

Tj: I like you too

Cyrus: I don’t think you’re getting this. I like boys. I like like you as in a not just as a friend way and it’s completely okay if you don’t feel the same way! I completely understand if you don’t because I know that we’re friends and-

Tj: Hey Cyrus! *shakes Cyrus’ hand that he’s holding to get his attention* I like like you too.

Cyrus: oh

And then they both stare at eachother in silence and Cyrus has the biggest smile on his face and then they hug and they’re 0 feet appart cuz they’re so gay (also I feel like Cyrus would be ramblings a lot and nervous)

tags: i mean cyrus is a big step in the right direction but theres still much more progress to be made with lgbt rep in youth media
summary: Do you think tyrus will still be angsty after they’re together?
question: Do you think tyrus will still be angsty after they’re together?
answer:
I don’t know. And since they’re likely not going to even admit their feelings until the series finale, I guess we’ll never know 🤷🏻‍♀️

Here’s to hoping the next progressive kids/teen show steps it up and actually allows a main LGBT character to have a relationship on screen
